  "MICROPHONE QUALITY CONTROL": {
   "width": 13620,
   "height": 8062,
   "color": "rgb(133,156,252)",
   "labels": [
    {
     "text": " A-IVI2 shall perform Microphone quality control following details below. Organe To be controlled: stand alone microphone Function to be performed:  Supplier to define the strategy for microphone quality test When a sound is requested, ECU must:  Mute all sources  Issue the requested sound  Activate microphone  Return to normal state It must not be possible to issue a tone to more than one (1) loudspeaker.  A-IVI2 must be capable to analyze the incoming sound compared to the outcoming one.",
     "color": "rgb(255,128,128)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 960,
      "top": 120,
      "height": 4192,
      "width": 12120
