  "CONFIGURATION HASH": {
   "width": 13620,
   "height": 7996,
   "color": "rgb(133,156,252)",
   "labels": [
    {
     "text": "AIVI2 shall perform the CONFIGURATION HASH routine as defined below : Organe to be controlled: AIVI2 Function to be performed: On start routine , the system must start the hash of the DIDs coding strings with positive response \"Routine in progress\". On completion of the Routine , the ECU must send positive reponse with status\" Routine Completed\"  If this hash does not correspond to the hash reference , then the DTC should be raised. Conditions:  -Writing is completed for all DIDs used in the config. -It is written in the non-volatile memory, and it should be calculated using the DATA of the non-volatile memory. ",
     "color": "rgb(255,128,128)",
     "alignment": "0",
